WIFS Northeast Florida invites you to join us for Lunch!

 

  Current Issues in Estate Planning for 2013

 

Tuesday, January 8th

 BlackFinn American Grille

11:30-1:00 pm

   

 The 2013 New Year marks the 3rd consecutive year in which estate and gift tax laws are in a state of substantial flux.  Exemption amounts and rates have changed unpredictably and ranged widely in the last several years. The New Year is expected to herald substantial new changes once again. 

Join WIFS NE FL for lunch as Jeff Cramer with Cramer Law Center reviews the current issues in Estate Planning for 2013.  Jeff will provide a practical guide to major changes in the estate and gift tax law, planning opportunities under the new tax regime, and a discussion of how changed law impacts existing plans.

 

 

Jeffrey A. Cramer holds an undergraduate degree from Vanderbilt University and a Doctor of Jurisprudence (J.D.), with honors, from the University of Florida College of Law, where he served on the Editorial Board of the Law Review.  He has been admitted to practice law in all state and federal courts in Florida.  With more than 34 years experience as a civil trial lawyer, Jeff successfully has handled a wide variety of personal injury and employment-discrimination claims, contract and family disputes, as well as probate and guardianship contests in both trial and appellate courts.  Jeff also has been an adjunct professor of employment law at Florida Coastal School of Law, a frequent lecturer at continuing legal education seminars and has published several articles on civil trial issues.

Jeff has been certified by the Florida Supreme Court as both a circuit court and family mediator. He has received the highest rating from his peers, “AV” by the Martindale-Hubbell Company, is listed in the “Bar Register of Preeminent Lawyers” and “Who’s Who in American Law”.  Jeff has served as Escambia-Santa Rosa County Bar Association President and both as Northwest Florida Chapter President and member of the National Board of Directors of the prestigious American Board of Trial Advocates.

The extensive trial experience gathered from handling thousands of diverse civil matters has provided the skills necessary for Jeff to embark on the next phase of his career, helping people and families to plan effectively for their future.  Jeff undertook a several month course of intensive study of all facets of estate planning and now focuses his law practice on estate planning, estate administration (including probate), guardianship and elder law.  He is a member of the National Network of Estate Planning Attorneys, an experienced, cutting-edge group of forward thinking lawyers who collaborate and educate on the latest estate planning laws and techniques.  Jeff also is a certified legacy advisor helping clients pass on their wisdom along with their wealth. As a result, his law practice now offers clients the combination of the support of a group of experienced estate planning colleagues from around the country along with Jeff’s own extensive legal background and experience.

The Holidays are right around the corner and it's time to celebrate the year!

 

The 1st Annual Jolly Holly Party is here and you're invited!

 

Kick off the holiday season with the hippest jingle hop in town, complete with holiday libations, photo ops with the big guy and dance music sure to make you shake your sleigh bells! 

$15 online/$20 at the door

Online ticket sales end at 2:00 PM on November 21, 2012

 

21 year old entry and older only


Drinks available for purchase (Cash only bar; ATM available)

All tickets include a Jolly Holly good time! 

 

Costumes strongly encouraged (or find yourself on Santa’s naughty list)!

The holiday costume possibilities are endless.  Here’s your chance to get creative and dress festive.  Tights, wrapping paper, lights, reindeer antlers, mistletoe, Santa hats, holiday sweaters—it’s all welcomed! Don’t be the only one without a costume!

 

Come celebrate the holidays with the 1st Annual Jolly Holly Party!

 

Unsure about holiday costume ideas? Google the following phrases and check out the images—we guarantee you’ll be inspired.

 

“Christmas present costume” – “reindeer costume” – “nutcracker costume” – “Christmas tree costume” – “gingerbread man costume” – “candy cane costume” – “dreidel costume” – “snowman costume” – “snowflake costume”

 

All proceeds from the Jolly Holly party will benefit Partnership 4 Kids, an Omaha non-profit working to turn Omaha’s cycle of poverty and failure into one of achievement and prosperity.  Partnership 4 Kids’ mission is to partner with the community to guide youth toward academic success, from kindergarten to careers, through goal setting, mentoring, and college access programs.  Currently there are more than 5,000 students in 22 Omaha Public Schools participating in Partnership programs.  For more information, visit www.p4k.org.

 

 

Music provided by DJ Lucas Krance

Photography provided by Terrence Tryon Photography

Drinks provided by Lucky Bucket

Eligibility: The O’Daniel Jeep Jam Cornhole Event is open to any persons 12 years of age or older. Individuals ranked as Super-Pro or Pro Caliber as listed on the American Cornhole Organization website are not eligible to play. Those ranked as semi-pro and amateurs will be permitted.

 

Registration: The O’Daniel group will accept team registrations beginning September 25th. Teams will be accepted into the tournament until October 12th or when 50 teams officially register, whichever occurs first. Each team will pay a $25 registration fee before the entry will be accepted. Players must register in teams of two players. Single entries will not be accepted. Registration fees are non-refundable. 

 

Registration Deadlines: Entries received by mail will be accepted based on the date the entry is received at O’Daniel Auto Group. 

Registration Refunds: Refunds will ONLY be given to teams if they meet one of the criterion listed below:

The tournament reaches 50 teams and your registration was accepted online after that time.

Registration fees will NOT be refunded for any other reason. If a team pays the registration fee and becomes unable to participate at a later date, the registration fee is forfeited. 

 

Tournament Style: The ODZ Jeep Jam Cornhole Event will be played as a single elimination bracket tournament. On Saturday, October 13th 50 teams will compete in a bracket tournament. During tournament play each team will play their assigned opponent at their assigned time (competitors are chosen at random prior to the tournament) If any team is more than 10 minutes late FOR ANY REASON, the team will forfeit their participation and a stand-by team will be accepted for the remainder of the tournament. Teams will play best-2-out-of-3 games to 21 points. This guarantees each team at least 2 games during the tournament.  Players will be responsible for keeping their score using the scoring devices provided at each cornhole game set.  There will be no Skunk rule in this tournament.

 

Prizes: One (1) grand prize of half of all money raised from the cornhole tournament will be given.  For instance, if 50 teams register at $25 per team, the grand prize would be $625.  

 

Cornhole Game Rules: The ODZ Jeep Jam Cornhole Event will be played and operated by the official cornhole rules as regulated by the American Cornhole Organization (ACO). These rules can be found at www.americancornhole.org. ODZ highly suggests that all players review these rules and be familiar with them prior to playing in our tournament.  All ACO game rules will be strictly enforced with the exception of the Skunk rule. Players are responsible for making themselves aware of the scoring, fouls and general game rules associated with Cornhole prior to taking part in the tournament.

Important Note! 

Please remember to start your tour at 2326 Esplanade Ave on Saturday November 3rd and 4725 Dauphine St on Sunday November 4th. These locations will have your tickets, wristbands, maps and commemorative posters!

Art Home New Orleans is once again opening doors to the city's elegant and eclectic homes and studios for the 3rd Annual weekend of tours presented by the Creative Alliance of New Orleans, (CANO). This is one of the nation's largest tours, this year of over 40 homes and studios.

What: Art Home New Orleans is an annual self-guided public tour, this year on November 3rd and 4th from 12-5pm. The tour highlights emerging artists as well as works in private art collections. One participant said of last year’s tour: “You can go to galleries and museums anytime, but to meet the artists and see the art in private collections brings out the essence of the city.”

When and Where: The tour includes homes and studios citywide on Saturday, November 3rd and in the Lower 9th Ward on Sunday, November 4th, from 12pm to 5pm on both days. Some of the artists included this year are Prospect.2’s Bruce Davenport Jr., blacksmith Rachel David, painter Nicole Charbonnet, sculptor, Clifton Webb, photographers Kevin Kline, and Christopher Porche West, the home of Enrique Alferez’s daughter Tlaloc Alferez and many more!

Also enjoy "wrap parties" at the end of the tours at Casa Borrega, 1719 Oretha Castle Haley Boulevard at 5pm on Saturday, and at the Art House on the Levee, 4725 Dauphine Street, at 5pm on Sunday night.

How: With the purchase of tickets, tour participants receive a map that guides them through the city visiting these vibrant, private locations. Tickets are $15/day and $25/weekend. Student tickets are $10/day. Tickets can be purchased online at arthome2012..com or by coming to 2326 Esplanade Ave on Saturday and 4725 Dauphine St on Sunday to pick up tickets.

See a teaser video of this year's tour here:http://vimeo.com/52509360

Why:  The current New Orleans cultural scene is now characterized by unprecedented innovation and collaboration.  CANO wants to make this new scene and work more accessible to visitors and residents alike. Art Home New Orleans  (1) Enriches the New Orleans cultural experience of visitors and residents and broadens their understanding of the city's rich cultural legacy and new artistic offerings, encouraging repeat visits; (2) showcases the work of New Orleans based artists of all disciplines in visual, design, media, performing and culinary arts; and (3) helps demystify the "art" of collecting, encouraging the collection of the art works of area artists.

Who: Creative Alliance of New Orleans in partnership with artists and art collectors throughout New Orleans. CANO's mission is to provide training, education, and information for creative artists, cultural producers and the community, to protect our cultural legacy and to promote the revitalization of the city as a cultural and economic center.

We also offer custom tours. For questions regarding booking a private tour, email Tori Bush at bush@cano-la.org or call 504.218.4807.

The Calgary Sports Convention, known as the YYC SportsCon, will be the first ever event of this calibre held in Canada, where the latest and greatest gadgets, companies, retailers, information from the sports industry will be on display under one roof.

There will also be celebrities/athletes attending, allowing fans an opportunity to get autographs and/or pictures with some of their favourite stars.

The convention will run from August 16th to August 18th, 2013. There are different ticket options available, allowing you to choose the one that best suits your needs.



FAQs

Are there ID requirements or an age limit to enter the event?

No, there is no age limit. However, there are different ticket prices for different ages.

 

What are my transport/parking options getting to the event?

You can use the Calgary Transit to get to Stampede Park, or you may park at the Stampede Grounds for a fee.

 

Where can I contact the organizer with any questions?

If you have any questions, you can send them to contact@yycsportscon.com, and put the heading "Tickets" in the subject line of your email. We will do our best to respond to you within 48 hours.

 

Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?

Yes, you will need to show your printed ticket at the door to gain admission to the Big Four Building, where YYC SportsCon is being held.

 

What if I bought tickets, but can't go anymore. Can I give/sell them to a friend?

Although the name of the individual that purchased the ticket shows up on there, the barcodes are unique so you can give it to anybody you like. We can still track them.


What if I bought tickets, but can't go anymore. Can I get a refund?

Unfortunately, there are no refunds or exchanges on any tickets purchased. This applies to any and all circumstances, unless the convention is canceled by the hosting company. If that happens, then all ticket purchases will be refunded to all ticket purchasers within 30 business days.

Nationally, regionally, and locally, we are here to attract, develop, and advance the careers of women in the financial services industry.

Women in Insurance & Financial Services (WIFS) is the ONLY national organization exclusively devoted to helping women succeed in both insurance and financial services.  No matter your tenure, if you are a producer, independent or captive, or in management in these industries, we invite you to join Women In Insurance and Financial Services.  As the preeminent professional organization for women in the financial services industry, WIFS is dedicated to attracting capable women to the financial services sector, helping them develop their talents and advancing them toward their fullest potential.

To Support, Encourage and Advance the Success of Women in the Financial Services Industry. Most importantly, the group has built a strong network of women helping each other develop the success that lies within each of us.
 
Membership meetings are held every other ODD month.
